problem:
In the figure, point $O$ is the center of the circle, the measure of angle $RTB$ is 28 degrees, and the measure of angle $ROB$ is three times the measure of angle $SOT$. What is the measure of minor arc $RS$, in degrees? [asy]
unitsize(1.2cm);
defaultpen(linewidth(.7pt)+fontsize(8pt));
dotfactor=3;

pair A=(0,0), B=(-1,0), T=(2,0);
pair T0=T+10*dir(162);
pair[] RS=intersectionpoints(Circle(A,1),T--T0);
pair Sp=RS[0];
pair R=RS[1];
pair[] dots={A,B,T,Sp,R};
dot(dots);

draw(Circle(A,1));
draw(B--T--R);

label("$T$",T,S);
label("$O$",A,S);
label("$B$",B,W);
label("$R$",R,NW);
label("$S$",Sp,NE);
[/asy]

solution:
Let $C$ be the point where line segment $\overline{OT}$ intersects the circle.

[asy]
unitsize(1.2cm);
defaultpen(linewidth(.7pt)+fontsize(8pt));
dotfactor=3;
pair A=(0,0), B=(-1,0), T=(2,0), C=(1,0);
pair T0=T+10*dir(162);
pair[] RS=intersectionpoints(Circle(A,1),T--T0);
pair Sp=RS[0];
pair R=RS[1];
pair[] dots={A,B,T,Sp,R,C};
dot(dots);
draw(Circle(A,1));
draw(B--T--R);
label("$T$",T,S);
label("$O$",A,S);
label("$B$",B,W);
label("$R$",R,NW);
label("$S$",Sp,NE);
label("$C$",C,SE);[/asy]

Since $\angle ROB = 3\angle SOT = 3\angle SOC$, the measure of arc $RB$ is three times the measure of arc $SC$. We also have  \[\angle RTB = \frac{\widehat{RB} - \widehat{SC}}{2}.\] Letting the measure of $\widehat{SC}$ be $x$, we have $\angle RTB = (3x-x)/2 = x$, so $x= 28^\circ$.  Therefore, we have $\widehat{RB} = 3x = 84^\circ$ and $\widehat{SC}=28^\circ$.  Since $\widehat{BC}$ is a semicircle, we have $\widehat{RS} = 180^\circ - \widehat{RB} -\widehat{SC} = 180^\circ - 84^\circ - 28^\circ = \boxed{68^\circ}$.
